data.title: Double Dragon [Arcade/Atari/Commodore/Nintendo/Sega; 1988
data.meta_description:
The opening theme to Double Dragon across several platforms.

Starts with the Arcade (YM2151 & MSM5205 sound chips)
1:45 - Atari 2600 & 7800 versions (both consoles used the same TIA sound chip)
2:31 - Atari Lynx version (8-bit DAC w/ 4ch sound)
3:19 - Commodore 64 version (SID chip). This version doesn't play the theme song, but instead uses the "Slum" soundtrack
4:11 - Nintendo Entertainment System Version (PSG Audio)
5:47 - Sega Master System Version (Sega PSG (SN76496) @ 3.57 MHz) - Note: This one really was only 17 seconds long
6:04 - Sega Master System, FM chip version (YM2413)
6:21 - Sega Genesis Version (PSG (TI 76489 chip) & FM chip (Yamaha YM 2612))
